<subSubSection id="AEF95CB2FF8BFFA930C3737025A2A286" pageId="37" pageNumber="238" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E65C0F39FF8BFFA930C3737025A2A286" blockId="37.[151,1437,1053,2022]" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="D497D32BFF8BFFA930C373702658A276" bold="true" box="[151,266,1053,1078]" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The only Neotropical species of the 
<taxonomicName id="21E374BAFF8BFFA932917370247FA276" box="[709,813,1053,1078]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Ceratopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mutabilis">mutabilis</taxonomicName>
group with males distinguished by the posteromedial surface of sternite 9 with medial wrinkles, a greatly curved gonostylus with pointed apex, symmetrical fused paramere and gonocoxal apodemes, and aedeagus with slender, heavily sclerotized, posterolateral arms with pointed tips and posteromedian projection with bifurcate distal portion. Females with a very large (length 118µm) elongate ovoid spermatheca with a very slender neck.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AEF95CB2FF8BFFAB309373BC26BBA72A" lastPageId="39" lastPageNumber="240" pageId="37" pageNumber="238" type="description">
<paragraph id="E65C0F39FF8BFFAA309373BC26EBA694" blockId="37.[151,1437,1053,2022]" lastBlockId="38.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="239" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="D497D32BFF8BFFA9309373BC2656A2AA" bold="true" box="[199,260,1233,1258]" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Male</emphasis>
. Head (
<figureCitation id="7ED813BCFF8BFFA9310F73BC26FEA2AA" box="[347,428,1233,1258]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1627,1649]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,265,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,265,1606]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 21. Dasyhelea megatheca n. sp. Holotype male, A – D, Allotype female, E – J. A, E. head. B, G. palpus. C, H. Wing. D. genitalia. F. frontal sclerite and clypeus. I. abdomen and spermatheca. J. subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164739/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
A). Dark brown. Eyes contiguous for a distance equal to the width of 2 ommatidia. Frontal sclerite elliptical, moderately short with a slender posterior extension extending to base of clypeus. Antennal flagellum with flagellomeres 2–9 rhomboid, 10–13 elongate, 13 broader than 10–12; flagellomeres 2–10 with single whorl of long sensilla chaetica comprising the dense plume that extends to near apex of flagellomere 12; antennal ratio 0.94–1.07 (0.98, n=10). Clypeus with 6 pairs of setae. Palpus (
<figureCitation id="7ED813BCFF8BFFA93443720C2339A33A" box="[1047,1131,1377,1402]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1627,1649]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,265,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,265,1606]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 21. Dasyhelea megatheca n. sp. Holotype male, A – D, Allotype female, E – J. A, E. head. B, G. palpus. C, H. Wing. D. genitalia. F. frontal sclerite and clypeus. I. abdomen and spermatheca. J. subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164739/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
B) light brown; segment 3 slender, as long as 4+5 combined with scattered capitate sensilla; palpal ratio 3.14–4.83 (3.89, n=10). Thorax. Dark brown. Scutellum with 6 large, 3 smaller setae. Wing (
<figureCitation id="7ED813BCFF8BFFA9337572C42424A382" box="[801,886,1449,1474]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1627,1649]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,265,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,265,1606]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 21. Dasyhelea megatheca n. sp. Holotype male, A – D, Allotype female, E – J. A, E. head. B, G. palpus. C, H. Wing. D. genitalia. F. frontal sclerite and clypeus. I. abdomen and spermatheca. J. subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164739/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
C) moderately slender; membrane hyaline with moderately dense macrotrichia; veins brown; 2nd radial cell moderately developed, slender with gap between apices of costa, radius; fork of CuA1 at level of base of 2nd radial cell; anal lobe well developed; wing length 0.76–0.86 (0.82, n=10) mm, width 0.28–0.32 (0.29, n=10) mm; costal ratio 0.46–0.51 (0.48, n=10). Abdomen. Dark brown. Genitalia (
<figureCitation id="7ED813BCFF8BFFA93159712C2638A01A" box="[269,362,1601,1626]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1627,1649]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,265,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,265,1606]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 21. Dasyhelea megatheca n. sp. Holotype male, A – D, Allotype female, E – J. A, E. head. B, G. palpus. C, H. Wing. D. genitalia. F. frontal sclerite and clypeus. I. abdomen and spermatheca. J. subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164739/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Figs. 21</figureCitation>
D, 22A). Tergite 9 broad on proximal half, distal half tapering progressively distally to rounded apex that extends to apices of gonocoxites; apicolateral process very short, conical with stout apical seta; cercus very small with 3–4 setae. Sternite 9 (
<figureCitation id="7ED813BCFF8BFFA9322B71E425B6A0E2" box="[639,740,1673,1698]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1627,1649]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,265,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,265,1606]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 21. Dasyhelea megatheca n. sp. Holotype male, A – D, Allotype female, E – J. A, E. head. B, G. palpus. C, H. Wing. D. genitalia. F. frontal sclerite and clypeus. I. abdomen and spermatheca. J. subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164739/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Figs. 21</figureCitation>
D, 22B) moderately long, 0.46 length of greatest width; posteromedian portion broad proximally, distal half tapering slightly with broad, slightly notched apex, medial surface with 4 elongate wrinkles. Gonocoxite stout, twice as long as broad, broadest distally, apicomesal surface with group of dense, moderately long setae; gonostylus 0.86 length of gonocoxite, proximal 1/3 broad at base, gradually tapered, distal 2/3 slender, greatly curved, apex slightly broader with pointed tip. Paramere and gonocoxal apodemes (
<figureCitation id="7ED813BCFF8BFFA931C1705026BAA116" box="[405,488,1853,1878]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1975,1997]" captionTargetBox="[218,1375,467,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[202,1385,450,1953]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 22. Dasyhelea megatheca n. sp. Holotype male. A. genitalia. B. sternite 9. C. gonocoxal apodemes and paramere. D. aedeagus. Scale bar: 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164740/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
C) forming a symmetrical structure; gonocoxal apodemes sinuate, stout proximally, tapering distally; paramere very slender, extending to apex of aedeagus. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="7ED813BCFF8BFFA93423700C239FA13A" box="[1143,1229,1889,1914]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1975,1997]" captionTargetBox="[218,1375,467,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[202,1385,450,1953]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 22. Dasyhelea megatheca n. sp. Holotype male. A. genitalia. B. sternite 9. C. gonocoxal apodemes and paramere. D. aedeagus. Scale bar: 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164740/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
D) 0.60 length of greatest width; basal arch low, lightly sclerotized, anterior margin slightly convex, distal margin with rounded excavation; posterolateral arms heavily sclerotized, convergent, broad proximally, tapering abruptly distally to slender apex with sharply pointed tips that almost touch; posteromedian projection with semi-triangular proximal portion, overlapping to basal arch, distal portion deeply bifurcate, with slender distal processes that extend just beyond apex of sternite 9.
</paragraph>
<caption id="B29C5FB1FF88FFAA30C37136234FA0D0" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164739/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="239" targetBox="[151,1435,265,1605]" targetPageId="38">
<paragraph id="E65C0F39FF88FFAA30C37136234FA0D0" blockId="38.[151,1436,1627,1680]" pageId="38" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="D497D32BFF88FFAA30C37136264DA030" bold="true" box="[151,287,1627,1649]" pageId="38" pageNumber="239">FIGURE 21.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="21E374BAFF88FFAA317071362551A031" box="[292,515,1627,1649]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Dasyhelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megatheca" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="D497D32BFF88FFAA317071362551A031" box="[292,515,1627,1649]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="239">
<taxonomicName id="21E374BAFF88FFAA3170713626DDA031" box="[292,399,1627,1649]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Dasyhelea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dasyhelea</taxonomicName>
megatheca
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CFA46E50FF88FFAA325D71312513A031" box="[521,577,1628,1649]" pageId="38" pageNumber="239" rank="species">
<emphasis id="D497D32BFF88FFAA325D71312513A031" bold="true" box="[521,577,1628,1649]" pageId="38" pageNumber="239">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Holotype male, A–D, Allotype female, E–J. A, E. head. B, G. palpus. C, H. Wing. D. genitalia. F. frontal sclerite and clypeus. I. abdomen and spermatheca. J. subgenital plate.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="E65C0F39FF88FFAB309371DA26BBA72A" blockId="38.[151,1437,1719,2002]" lastBlockId="39.[151,1436,151,398]" lastPageId="39" lastPageNumber="240" pageId="38" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="D497D32BFF88FFAA309371DA264CA090" bold="true" box="[199,286,1719,1744]" pageId="38" pageNumber="239">Female</emphasis>
. Head (
<figureCitation id="7ED813BCFF88FFAA312F71DA269CA090" box="[379,462,1719,1744]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1627,1649]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,265,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,265,1606]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 21. Dasyhelea megatheca n. sp. Holotype male, A – D, Allotype female, E – J. A, E. head. B, G. palpus. C, H. Wing. D. genitalia. F. frontal sclerite and clypeus. I. abdomen and spermatheca. J. subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164739/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="239">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
E). Dark brown. Eyes contiguous for a distance equal to the width of 2.5 ommatidia. Frontal sclerite (
<figureCitation id="7ED813BCFF88FFAA310171B626FAA0B4" box="[341,424,1755,1780]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1627,1649]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,265,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,265,1606]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 21. Dasyhelea megatheca n. sp. Holotype male, A – D, Allotype female, E – J. A, E. head. B, G. palpus. C, H. Wing. D. genitalia. F. frontal sclerite and clypeus. I. abdomen and spermatheca. J. subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164739/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="239">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
F) similar to male. Antennal flagellum with flagellomeres 2–8 vasiform, slightly longer than broad, 11–14 slightly longer than 2–8, 13 longest; antennal ratio 0.85–0.96 (0.90, n=3). Clypeus (
<figureCitation id="7ED813BCFF88FFAA3565719222D1A158" box="[1329,1411,1791,1816]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1627,1649]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,265,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,265,1606]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 21. Dasyhelea megatheca n. sp. Holotype male, A – D, Allotype female, E – J. A, E. head. B, G. palpus. C, H. Wing. D. genitalia. F. frontal sclerite and clypeus. I. abdomen and spermatheca. J. subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164739/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="239">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
F) with 11 pairs of setae. Palpus (
<figureCitation id="7ED813BCFF88FFAA3250704E250AA17C" box="[516,600,1827,1852]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1627,1649]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,265,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,265,1606]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 21. Dasyhelea megatheca n. sp. Holotype male, A – D, Allotype female, E – J. A, E. head. B, G. palpus. C, H. Wing. D. genitalia. F. frontal sclerite and clypeus. I. abdomen and spermatheca. J. subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164739/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="239">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
G) brown; segment 3 about as long as 4+5 combined with 2–3 capitate sensilla on basomesal surface; palpal ratio 3.12–3.71 (3.36, n=3). Thorax. Scutum dark brown; scutellum paler with 6 large, 4 smaller setae. Femora, tibiae brown, tarsi slightly paler; hind tibial comb with 6 spines, 2nd longest; prothoracic tarsal ratio 1.62–1.94 (1.80, n=3), mesothoracic tarsal ratio 1.92–2.11 (2.01, n=3), metathoracic tarsal ratio 1.95–2.10 (2.03, n=3). Wing (
<figureCitation id="7ED813BCFF88FFAA327970D425D2A191" box="[557,640,1977,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1627,1649]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,265,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,265,1606]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 21. Dasyhelea megatheca n. sp. Holotype male, A – D, Allotype female, E – J. A, E. head. B, G. palpus. C, H. Wing. D. genitalia. F. frontal sclerite and clypeus. I. abdomen and spermatheca. J. subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164739/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="239">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
H) moderately broad; membrane hyaline with dense macrotrichia; 2nd radial cell reduced to a suture; apices of costa, radius at slight acute angle; fork of CuA1 at level of base of 2nd radial cell; wing length 0.72–0.74 (0.73, n=3) mm, width 0.32–0.34 (0.33, n=3) mm; costal ratio 0.50–0.53 (0.51, n=3) mm. Halter pale. Abdomen (Fig. (
<figureCitation id="7ED813BCFF89FFAB324A77882520A6BE" box="[542,626,229,254]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1627,1649]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,265,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,265,1606]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 21. Dasyhelea megatheca n. sp. Holotype male, A – D, Allotype female, E – J. A, E. head. B, G. palpus. C, H. Wing. D. genitalia. F. frontal sclerite and clypeus. I. abdomen and spermatheca. J. subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164739/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="240">
Fig. 
<date id="925D29F9FF89FFAB3200778B2520A6BE" box="[596,626,230,254]" pageId="39" pageNumber="240" value="1921-01">21</date>
</figureCitation>
I). Dark brown. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation id="7ED813BCFF89FFAB33A777882314A6BE" box="[1011,1094,229,254]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1627,1649]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,265,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,265,1606]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 21. Dasyhelea megatheca n. sp. Holotype male, A – D, Allotype female, E – J. A, E. head. B, G. palpus. C, H. Wing. D. genitalia. F. frontal sclerite and clypeus. I. abdomen and spermatheca. J. subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164739/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="240">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
J) sub-circular, posteromedian margin rounded; posterolateral arms slender, nearly straight. Spermatheca (
<figureCitation id="7ED813BCFF89FFAB33AC7664231EA762" box="[1016,1100,265,290]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1627,1649]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,265,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,265,1606]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 21. Dasyhelea megatheca n. sp. Holotype male, A – D, Allotype female, E – J. A, E. head. B, G. palpus. C, H. Wing. D. genitalia. F. frontal sclerite and clypeus. I. abdomen and spermatheca. J. subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164739/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="240">
Fig. 
<date id="925D29F9FF89FFAB34647667231EA762" box="[1072,1100,266,290]" pageId="39" pageNumber="240" value="1921-01">21</date>
</figureCitation>
I) large, elongate ovoid, very heavily sclerotized with moderately thick walls, length/width 118 
<date id="925D29F9FF89FFAB33DB76432490A706" box="[911,962,301,326]" pageId="39" pageNumber="240" value="1964-10">x 64</date>
µm, neck moderately long, very slender, slightly curved, length 10 µm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
